113 (e)(1) The legislative members of the task force, if
114 any, shall be entitled to their legislative compensation, per
115 diem, and travel expenses for each day they attend a meeting
116 of the task force pursuant to Section 49 of the Constitution
117 of Alabama of 2022.
118 (2) The nonlegislative members of the task force shall
119 serve without compensation but may be reimbursed for necessary
120 expenses in attending meetings of the task force pursuant to
121 the policies of their appointing authority.
122 Section 8. This act shall become effective on July 1,
123 2027.
